description:
Boom! Bang! Sound effect! BPM returns in triumphant fashion: one year down, countless adventures to go! Delve back into the worlds of Cuckoos, Orb, 99 Swords and Cat & Meringue in this kinda new, somewhat different edition of BPM. (P.S. Check out our new design. We're rather pleased with it.)

Inside! The crew of the Reflektor find themselves stranded in an unknown universe gripped in ceaseless global war. A young girl's connection to the mysterious alien entity known as the Orb grows. Elsie Blackwood has cause to regret her new career path in the world of 99 Swords. And Cat & Meringue enter the time stream in search of their origin story!

Jax and his band of misfits have bitten off more than they can chew after an ancient army awakens upon their arrival. They must fight their way through the horde and learn the secrets the ancient people hid in their temple long ago. The men have to decide what price they are willing to pay for handing a powerful relic over to a man they don't know.
Fourth book in the Havenhurst series: a flashback to an uneasy childhood.

John L. Sullivan is back in training for the next opponent. As usual he is a tough pupil to teach. His headstrong ways and know-it-all attitude cause a constant friction between Buque and himself. It reaches a boiling point where the 2 come to blows. Mrex watches with Dawk and is fine with the friction as long as he gets the results he wants; the last thing he wants is a bond between the 2. John learns about Buques past from Dawk, the history of his ascent and ultimate downfall to his current state of captive trainer. John L. softens a bit and offers Buque an olive branch in the form of synthetic beer and promises to work with him and not be fighting him at every turn.

volume.name: John L. Sullivan Boston Strong Boy In Space

description: Lilly has finally been given a chance to escape the greasy hoosegow that is Ovenland, but she still might be in for the fight of her young life.

3 Monsters And A Baby

Taking care of a baby can be monstrous...

Three bumbling monster criminals on the run from the law accidentally wind up as babysitters. But they've got bigger problems than diapers because that baby is being hunted by Dracula and an army of vampires.

This lightning-paced one-shot from Source Point Press delivers chills and laughs for monster-lovers from age 9 to 999.
name: Three Monsters And A Baby

description:
The series continues with this 10 page edition! At full size this 17 x 22" paper is quite impressive! The next best thing to viewing original art.

Included here is Nexus Comic Strips #9-11 plus pages from "When She was Young", a fully painted story fearing Sundra Peale in her college days that was originally published in Nexus 100. Also featured are extras including pencils, notes and color stage progress.

Rob Hanes and the Pirates

After Rob uncovers a counterfeit ring in Asia, he is abducted by a longtime nemesis and imprisoned in one of the most impregnable totalitarian regimes in the world. Escape seems hopeless until Rob befriends a kidnapped television star, a disaffected military officer, and an American soldier who defected during the Cold War...
name: Rob Hanes and the Pirates

description:
I am Rubber, you are...?

With Awesome-Gal missing and a city in chaos, how is our hero going to save the day!? Will RubberMan ever get out of this mess on his own? How will our hero defeat those villains, save Saturn City and find his friend Guma? Now is the time to find out all these answers in the final episode!
name: I Am Rubber, You Are...?

description:
Slingers Three

Welcome to the Swinging Sixties...

A.D. 2963

SLINGERS is science-fiction adventure with a sixties aesthetic. The Rat Pack in space. DM and Frank are two wartime buddies now trying to make their way in a post-war world. DM is staying out of trouble for the sake of his fianc√©e, Jeannie, but Frank is finding it harder to stay on the straight and narrow. Despite their best intentions, they are about to be set on a new path where trouble finds them...

Requiem for The King pt1

Rigby and Cliff learn more about being Soul Men as they learn about what drives the soul of of Mozart! The King tries to figure out why the heck Gerald has faith in Rigby and Cliff.
name: Requiem for The King pt1

description: It's time to go home...
name: Chapter Five

description: The future of the Terminus Project is hanging by a thread. Will the new team member prove acceptable to the rest of the group?

Freedom to Live

As Doktor Bleak gets a surprise visit on Mars, everything comes together for a startling finale that spans time and space.
name: Chapter 8: Freedom to Live

description: A young girl is given a book about a hero who must go on a quest to save a great tree from darkness. Only, the story isn't finished and must get an author, who doesn't believe himself, to finish the book.
name: Chapter 1

description: A giant slug monster is is leaving a path of chaos and destruction across its path. Its up to one hero to protect the good people of Century City. That man, Ace Maxwell.

Welcome to Bug Village! This sleepy little village is home to Stag-B and Rhino-B, aka the Bug Boys! These two best friends love adventure and exploring the nooks and crannies of Bug Village, the surrounding forest, and their own minds. Along the way, they meet new bug friends (like spooky Dome Spider and shy Dragonfly), face their fears (Bees! Termites! Self-doubt!!), and see their friendship grow ever stronger. Bug Village is much bigger than it seems, let's explore!

350 pages of all-ages fun and adventure, Bug Boys vol. 1 collects every issue of Bug Boys to date!
name: Volume 1: Welcome to Bug Village

description:
An action packed comic book adventure with a finful of fish puns!

As a devious doctor plots to create an army of brainwashed gamers for his own nefarious ends, the world's finest porpoise crime fighters must face shocking revelations from their past!

Seventy-two full-colour pages including a bonus section, The Dynamic Dolphins: The Story of Dolphin Squad.

volume.name: Dolphin Squad - Heroes of the Sea

description:
Bigfoot, Jersey Devil, Choop, and Nessy are back in this all-new one-shot featuring three thrilling tales of the famous Footprints gang!

"Bad Luck Charm" is a throwback story to the glory days of the team as Jersey Devil and Motheresa take a gambling trip to Rat Pack-era Las Vegas.

"Ghost on the Road" is the first follow-up tale to Footprints Vol. 1 as the gang finds themselves in the swamps of South Carolina on the hunt for a mysterious creature called the Lizard Man.

And finally, Foot takes to the mean streets of New York City during the reign of the Son of Sam killer in the first-ever Footprints prose tale, "Mr. Monster!"

In a dozen stories Malachi explores and blends the classic themes of fantasy and science fiction using a range of illustration techniques and styles. In "Utu" a Shaman arrives at an outpost with prognostications of a terrible war. He claims his visions come from a mysterious god, but can he be trusted? In "Hero for Science" a time-travelling rescue mission turns dour when a team member goes native. In "The Scout" while retrieving information in a remote cave, a scout encounters another version of himself.

Prepare for a full-frontal behind-the-scenes look at the monumental Gold Digger special Gina Diggers: WarNerd of Mars! Creator Fred Perry shares a variety of character designs, drawing stages, sketches, and insights about creating the Bazooms of Barsoom!

volume.name: Gina Diggers: Warnerd of Mars - Bonus Issue Full Moons of Mars

description:
Lila

Johnny's night of scotch soaked introspection goes from bad to worse when Lila walks in the door trailed by a pack of testosterone fueled thugs. He will have to work hard to make it out alive and with the girl.
name: Lila

description:
Helping Hands for Lost Souls

Finding themselves in a strange land, a dark adventure awaits two young siblings.
name: Helping Hands for Lost Souls

description:
For millennia, the energies of the Zodiac have been available to those whose consciousness is open to the reception and manipulation of them.

That access has been achieved by one person for each of the houses of the celestial wheel. This is the saga of the NEW ZODIAX!

Volume 1 introduces you to the first FOUR members of the NEW ZODIAX universe: the New Aquarius, the LIBERAIDER--a gifted teenage hacker who becomes the Robin Hood of Cyberspace--the New Pisces, CRICKET, who can communicate with the dead trapped on earth--MULTAA, the New Sagittarius--a colossal volcano monster who protects the last bastion of civilization in the galaxy, and The New Leo,The LION--the First Stargazer!

NEW ZODIAX Volume 1 collects issues #1 thru #4 of the original comics series, with added bonus materials!

Created by Joe St.Pierre (Marvel, DC, Image, Valiant, IDW).
name: Vol. 1

description:
This Graphic Novel contains 150 pages of Oops Comic Adventure plus extra content!

Oops is a young street rat in the medieval city of Casselberry, longing to find his family and where he belongs. After the lost of his only friend, a rat named Plague, he learns he has magical powers through accidentally reviving him. However, magic is heavily forbidden and the Evil King Hectric Tepper has landed his sights on Oops.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The year is 2099 and a devastating war that lasted for almost 20 years is coming to an end - a war between humans and evos, a new race that emerged from the ashes of a biological attack on the entire earth. World War 3 as they call it shall be remembered as the last war on the entire planet, as a world peace treaty has been signed by all nations that remained.

Jara Bint Rih was a soldier in this war - fighting for America, the place of her birth and a world free of oppression for everyone, human and mutant alike. But that belief cost her dearly. In an attack on her convoy she and her comrades were slaughtered. Most died and her spine was destroyed. Now she is confined to a wheelchair - alive but disgraced.

Living alone in the poor district of New York she spends her days in her friend Lucia's garage, searching for remnants from the past. But her world is about to change forever...
name: Vol. 1

description: The beautiful city of Hasenpfeffer, USA, is made a little less beautiful as the feud between the Smorgasbord Squad and H.U.N.G.E.R. Pack spills into the streets. And be amazed as the origins of the Smorgasbord Squad are explored as the details of the day the group came together are revealed!

Jasper works at a record shop. He‚Äôs a vegan since birth, whose life gets shaken when he gets bitten by a Vampire. He finds himself with a HUGE dilemma of trying to maintain his lifelong Vegan lifestyle and fighting his newly acquired THIRST for blood. He embarks on a journey with the help of his AWESOME grandma, to fight his way to a cure and prepares himself for a showdown with the Vamp who bit him.

The first issue in 5 years, but more than enough in this volume to make it worth the wait! This issue is stuffed with 100 pages of comics, paintings, prose, poetry and illustrations from 8 creators!

Included:

Almost 60 pages of new comics & art from John Linton Roberson, including the latest LULU, the first appearance since 2001 of UNCLE CYRUS, and the debut of the new satirical series SUZY SPREADWELL, as well as his acclaimed graphic version of the Billie Holiday classic "Strange Fruit" from GRAPHIC CANON 3, and illustrations for new writing from CHARLES ALVERSON (Story of Oh, Jabberwocky) and CHRIS DEWILDT!

26 pages of the brain-twisting paintings of the brilliant EMILY KAPLAN, the first collection of her work!

New poetry from CHAD PARENTEAU with illustrations from newcomer GIANNA RATTO!

A beautiful new cover by MOLLY KIELY!

And other surprises!

An astoundingly diverse collection mashing together many arts, check out the most gorgeous anthology of 2016 now!
name: Vol. 8

description:
Clowns.

To most, they are but bombastic buffoons, just mirthful madcaps.

But, at the vicious circus called Clown Town, they become avenging spirits for the abused, popping from the big top to cleanse their latest stop of those wretches who would harm the weak and exploit the innocent.

Dusty Gulch, Kentucky holds too many such monsters, and the circus has finally come to town.

96 pages of story, INCLUDING 6 bonus pages NOT included in the single issues!

When their ship crash lands on an uncharted planet, Grum and Zill set off in search of Zog. What they find is a world that hasn't been contacted in over a thousand years, and many species that are still very, very effected by that previous contact.

Where is Zog?

Grum and Zill don't know, but finding out is going to involve meeting a lot of large aliens who may or may not want to eat them.

Mondays

Scarlet begins her first day working for The Party as Conner is called in on his day off.

The giant-sized first 30 page issue!
name: Mondays

deck: Steel Beginning is the first Ukrainian tech-noir comic series. It's an eclectic mixture of several genres including fiction, post-punk and cyberpunk. Drawings are made in a classical 1980s style reminding of Robocop, Biker Mice from Mars, Transformers, Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Cops, SWAT Kats, etc. The action takes place in a parallel universe in a kind of infernal moto-city - a huge metropolis/small state. The story revolves around the former soldier and a lone wolf George Skyle.
description:
The comic book is drawn in tech-noir with color elements. It incorporates classical rock-style, punk and biker themes. The comic book is full of various allusions, adventures, detective stories and humour. It has a deep plot and raises social issues as well as the problems of a soldier at war. Series is supposed to be a cycle of several parts.

Readers will encounter a lot of surprises and also an unexpected ending, which they won't ever guess till the last page. Without further ado, Part I: Lone Wolf.
